is still very simple and there are a lot of features\nto add and some of them are very necessary stuff like time management.\u003c/p\u003e","tags":["Tonica","Zig","Chess"],"title":"TONICA"},{"categories":["Todo"],"date":"2024-11-29T00:00:00Z","id":"/notes/todos/wil/","keywords":[],"summary":"\u003ch2 id=\"programming-talks\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  Programming Talks\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#programming-talks\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w3WYdYyjek4\"\u003eTigerStyle\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"/notes/todos/done/tigerstyle/\" class=\"backlink\"\u003eNotes\u003c/a\u003e\n  \n  \n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","tags":["Programming"],"title":"Watch It Later"},{"categories":["Project"],"date":"2024-11-29T00:00:00Z","id":"/notes/projects/zhip8/zhip8/","keywords":[],"summary":"\u003cp\u003eChip-8 emulator in zig\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"what-is-chip8\" class=\"scroll-mt-8 group\"\u003e\n  What is chip8?\n  \n    \u003ca href=\"#what-is-chip8\"\n        class=\"no-underline hidden opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 !text-inherit group-hover:inline-block\"\n        aria-hidden=\"true\" title=\"Link to this heading\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg\n  xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"\n  width=\"16\"\n  height=\"16\"\n  fill=\"none\"\n  stroke=\"currentColor\"\n  stroke-linecap=\"round\"\n  stroke-linejoin=\"round\"\n  stroke-width=\"2\"\n  class=\"lucide lucide-link w-4 h-4 block\"\n  viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\n\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\" /\u003e\n  \u003cpath d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\" /\u003e\n\u003c/svg\u003e\n\n    \u003c/a\u003e\n  \n\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eChip-8 is a simple, interpreted, programming language which was first used on some do-it-yourself computer systems in the late 1970s and early 1980s. The COSMAC VIP, DREAM 6800, and ETI 660 computers are a few examples. These computers typically were designed to use a television as a display, had between 1 and 4K of RAM, and used a 16-key hexadecimal keypad for input. The interpreter took up only 512 bytes of memory, and programs, which were entered into the computer in hexadecimal, were even smaller.\u003c/p\u003e","tags":["Chip8","Zig"],"title":"Zhip-8"}]
